# Basic Example

::: columns
::: {.column width="80%"}

::: {.cell hash='index_cache/revealjs/unnamed-chunk-4_6d62e8512834312afd1ba9ebe9fcfc16'}

```{.r .cell-code}
survfit2(Surv(time, status) ~ surg, data = df_colon) |> 
  ggsurvfit() +
  add_risktable()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](index_files/figure-revealjs/unnamed-chunk-4-1.png){width=960}
:::
:::

:::
::: {.column width="20%"}
::: {.smaller}
::: {.incremental}

* The Good
  - Simple code and figure is nearly publishable
  - Risk table with both no. at risk and events easily added
  - x-axis label taken from the `time` column label
  - Can use **ggplot2** `+` notation


* The Could-Be-Better
  - Y-axis label is incorrect, and the range of axis is best 0-100%
  - Axis padding a bit more than I prefer for a Kaplan-Meier figure
  - X-axis typically has more tick marks for Kaplan-Meier figure

:::
:::
:::
:::

# Basic Example

::: {.cell hash='index_cache/revealjs/unnamed-chunk-5_d12ce1ddff7012501d1286a5eb3c8001'}

```{.r .cell-code}
survfit2(Surv(time, status) ~ surg, data = df_colon) |> 
  ggsurvfit() +
  add_risktable() +
  scale_ggsurvfit() +
  labs(y = "Recurrence-free Probability")
```

